docs.title:
(boolean, Dictionary) Has(<code>objects: Array&lt;string&gt;</code>) <p>Checks if the environment contains every specified index and returns a boolean and a dictionary with boolean values, example:     <pre><code>local hasAll, dictionary = treeEnv:Has({
    "Tree1",
    "Tree2",
    "Tree4"
})

print(hasAll, dictionary) -- output: false, { Tree1 = true, Tree2 = true, Tree4 = false }
</code></pre></p>

void Update(<code>objects: Dictionary&lt;string, any&gt;</code>) <p>Updates the objects with the specified index, example:     <pre><code>treeEnv:Update({
    Tree1 = treeEnv:Get("Tree2"),
    Tree2 = treeEnv:Get("Tree1"),
})
</code></pre></p>

